    <h2>How the Wheel Actually Works</h2>
    <p>
      Unlike software RNG casino games, Crazy Time uses a real physical wheel filmed by multiple HD cameras. The wheel is an actual mechanical device — not a computer simulation. This means the outcome is determined by physics, not an algorithm.
    </p>
    <p>
      The wheel is regularly tested and certified by independent testing labs (eCOGRA, GLI, BMM Testlabs) to verify that the segment frequencies match the published probabilities. Results must fall within statistical tolerances.
    </p>

    <h2>Why It Feels Rigged</h2>
    <p>
      Crazy Time feels rigged during losing streaks because of variance. High-variance games produce long runs without the result you expect. When the Crazy Time bonus does not hit for 80 rounds, it feels wrong — but this is normal probability at work, not manipulation.
    </p>
    <p>
      Our <a href="/crazy-time-predictor">live tracker</a> shows actual result frequencies against expected values. When you have real data, cold streaks look exactly like statistical variance — not rigging.
    </p>

